   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,881:               cli.py:  103: VAULT_COMPLETE_GUIDE.md
    INFO: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,886:         converter.py:   14: VAULT_COMPLETE_GUIDE.md
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Vault -- Complete Guide
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,900:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Your secure, local-first personal AI vault. All data encrypted on your machine.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,906:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What is Vault?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,912:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Vault is a personal AI agent that lives on your computer and acts as your encrypted digital memory. It stores your
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,914:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: identity documents, website passwords, and personal facts -- and gives them back when you ask, through natural
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,914:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: conversation.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,915:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What makes it different from a notes app or a password manager:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,916:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: It UNDERSTANDS your documents. You upload a scan of your Aadhaar card, and later ask 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,920:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,920:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s my Aadhaar number?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,921:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,922:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- it reads the text and answers.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,923:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,924:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: It works through conversation. You say 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,925:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,926:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Remember my blood type is O+
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,932:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,936:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  and it stores it. Later you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,938:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ask 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,940:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,942:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,946:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,958:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s my blood type?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,965:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,974:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  and it answers 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,981:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,984:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: O+
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,989:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,991:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: .
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:46,997:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,056:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: It is deeply private. Everything is encrypted with military-grade AES-256-GCM. Your passwords
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,061:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: never leave your machine. Not even your AI assistant sees them.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,063:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,074:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: It works as an MCP server, meaning any AI client you already use (Claude in Cursor, Claude
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,077:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Desktop, etc.) can access your vault through standard tools -- no separate app needed.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Big Picture: How Everything Fits Together
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,081:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Vault has three ways to interact with it:
