   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,294:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,295:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | vault
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,295:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: list
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,297:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: credentials | List saved services | No |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,299:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,299:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | vault
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,300:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,301:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: delete
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,301:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,302:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: credential | Remove a credential | No |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,302:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,303:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | vault
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,304:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,305:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: remember | Store
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,305:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a personal fact | No |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,306:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,306:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | vault
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,307:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,308:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: recall | Retrieve a personal fact | No |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,308:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,308:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | vault
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,309:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,309:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: list
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,309:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,310:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: facts | List all stored facts | No |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,310:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,310:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | vault
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,311:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,312:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: delete
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,313:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,313:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: fact | Remove a fact | No |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,314:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,314:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | vault
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: search | Search across everything | No |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Notice: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: none of these tools call any LLM.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,319:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  They are all pure local encrypted database operations. The AI reasoning
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,320:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: happens in whatever client is calling the tools (Claude, Cursor, etc.).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,321:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: MCP config for Cursor (already set up):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,321:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The file 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,322:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ~/.cursor/mcp.json
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,322:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  tells Cursor where to find the Vault MCP server:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,324:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,324:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   "mcpServers": {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,324:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     "vault": {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,325:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       "command": "/Users/anindyag/vault/.venv/bin/vault-mcp"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,325:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     }
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,326:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   }
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,327:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: }
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,327:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: When Cursor starts, it launches the 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,328:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault-mcp
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,329:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  process. This process runs the Vault MCP server using the 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,329:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: FastMCP
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,333:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  framework from the MCP Python SDK. It communicates with Cursor over stdin/stdout using the MCP
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,335:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: protocol (JSON-RPC messages). Cursor sends tool call requests, Vault processes them locally, and returns results.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,335:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2. Web UI
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,336:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A browser-based interface at http://127.0.0.1:8000 with:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,337:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,339:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Chat view
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,339:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- talk to Vault conversationally
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,340:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,341:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Documents view
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,341:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- browse stored documents as cards, upload via drag-and-drop
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,342:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,342:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Credentials view
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,343:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- see stored services and usernames
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,343:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,344:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Memory view
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,345:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- see all personal facts
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,345:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,346:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Lock screen
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,347:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- master password prompt
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,347:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,348:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Auto-lock
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,348:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- overlay appears when session times out
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,349:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Start it with 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,349:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault serve
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,350:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  in the terminal.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,352:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The web UI uses its own built-in LLM integration (OpenAI or Ollama) for the conversational part, unlike MCP
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,353:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mode where the client brings its own AI.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,354:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3. CLI (Terminal)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,354:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Direct commands for power users:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,355:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault init          # First-time setup
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,356:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault chat          # Interactive conversation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,356:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault store <file>  # Store a document
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,357:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault docs          # List documents
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,357:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault cred list     # List credentials
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,358:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault cred add      # Add a credential
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,359:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault facts         # List facts
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,359:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault mcp           # Start as MCP server
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,360:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault serve         # Start web UI
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,361:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault backup        # Encrypted backup
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,361:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault restore <file># Restore from backup
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,362:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault lock          # Lock immediately
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,362:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault unlock        # Unlock
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,363:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Security Design: How Your Data is Protected
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,364:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This is the most important section. Every design decision starts with security.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,365:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Encryption Chain
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,365:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: When you create your vault with 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,366:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault init
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,366:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , here
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,366:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,367:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s exactly what happens:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,368:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: YOU type a master password
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,368:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,369:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          v
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,369:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   +------------------+
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,370:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   | Argon2id KDF     |   Your password + random salt
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,370:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   | (memory-hard)    |   → 256-bit master key
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,376:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   | 64MB memory      |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,377:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   | 3 iterations     |   Takes ~0.5 seconds intentionally
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,378:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   | 4 parallel lanes |   (makes brute force impractical)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,378:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   +--------+---------+
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,379:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:            |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,379:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:            |  Master key is NEVER stored on disk.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,380:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:            |  It exists only in RAM while unlocked.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,380:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:            |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,381:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:      +-----+-----+-----+
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,381:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:      |           |           |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,382:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:      v           v           v
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,382:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  +-------+  +-------+  +-------+
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | DB    |  | File  |  | Cred  |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Key   |  | Key   |  | Key   |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,384:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  +---+---+  +---+---+  +---+---+
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,384:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:      |           |           |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,385:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:      v           v           v
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,385:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Encrypts    Encrypts    Encrypts
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,386:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  doc text,   raw files   passwords,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,386:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  facts,      (PDFs,      usernames,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,387:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  metadata    images)     login data
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,388:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Three separate keys are derived from the master key using BLAKE2b with unique domain separation tags. This
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,388:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: means:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,389:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,389:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Even if somehow the database key leaked, it can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,390:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,390:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t decrypt your files or credentials.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The credential key is completely isolated -- an extra layer of protection for your most sensitive data.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What Each Technology Does
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Argon2id
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- Password to key conversion. This is the algorithm that turns your master password into a 256-bit
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,395:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: encryption key. 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,395:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,396:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Memory-hard
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,396:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,405:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  means it deliberately uses 64MB of RAM during computation, which makes it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,410:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: extremely expensive for an attacker to try millions of passwords (even with GPUs or specialized hardware). It won
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,412:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the Password Hashing Competition in 2015 and is the current industry standard. The 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,413:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,413:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: id
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,414:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,415:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  variant is a hybrid that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,415:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: resists both side-channel attacks and GPU attacks.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,416:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: AES-256-GCM
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,419:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- The actual encryption. AES (Advanced Encryption Standard) with 256-bit keys is what
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,420:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: governments use for classified data. GCM (Galois/Counter Mode) adds authentication -- it doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,426:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t just encrypt, it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: also detects if anyone tampers with the encrypted data. Every piece of data gets a random 12-byte nonce (number
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,430:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: used once) so encrypting the same data twice produces different ciphertext.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,431:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: BLAKE2b
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,432:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- Key derivation from master key to purpose-specific keys. Faster than SHA-256 but equally secure.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,433:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Used here with 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,433:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,434:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: personalization
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,434:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,435:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  strings (like 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,435:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,435:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault-db-v1
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,436:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,436:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ) to derive different keys for different purposes from the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,437:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: same master key.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,437:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SQLite
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,438:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- The database that stores document metadata, encrypted text, encrypted facts, and encrypted credentials. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,438:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,441:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a single file on disk (vault.db). All sensitive fields are encrypted at the application level before being written to SQLite.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,441:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ChromaDB
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- Local vector database for semantic search. When you store a document, the extracted text is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: converted into a mathematical vector (embedding) that captures its meaning. When you search 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: identity documents
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,447:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , ChromaDB finds documents that are semantically related, even if they don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,449:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t contain those exact words. Runs 100%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,450:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: locally, no API calls.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,450:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: sentence-transformers
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,451:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- Creates the vector embeddings for ChromaDB. Uses the 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,451:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: all-MiniLM-L6-v2
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,453:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  model
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,454:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: which runs locally on your machine. Converts text into 384-dimensional vectors.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,454:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: PyMuPDF (fitz)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,456:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- Extracts text from PDF files. Opens the PDF, reads each page, and pulls out all the text content.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,456:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Runs locally, no network calls.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,457:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Tesseract OCR (via pytesseract)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,460:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- Optical Character Recognition for scanned images. When you upload a photo
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,461:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: of your Aadhaar card, Tesseract reads the text in the image. Runs locally. Requires 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,462:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: brew install tesseract
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,462:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,462:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: on Mac.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,463:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: FastAPI
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,465:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- The web framework powering both the web UI (HTML served at localhost:8000) and the API endpoints.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,465:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Lightweight, fast, async-capable Python framework.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,466:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: FastMCP
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,470:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- Part of the MCP Python SDK. Provides the decorator-based interface for defining MCP tools. Handles
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,471:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the JSON-RPC protocol, stdin/stdout communication with MCP clients, tool discovery, and argument validation.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,472:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: litellm
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,476:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- Unified interface for calling different LLM providers (OpenAI, Anthropic, Ollama). Used in the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: standalone CLI/web modes (not in MCP mode, where the client brings its own AI). A single 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: await
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: litellm.acompletion(model="gpt-4o-mini", ...)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  call works with any provider.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Typer + Rich
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,485:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- CLI framework. Typer handles command parsing and help text. Rich provides the colored output,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,485:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tables, and panels you see in the terminal.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,486:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Password Verification (Without Storing the Password)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,488:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Your master password is never stored. So how does Vault know if you typed the right password?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,488:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: During 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,489:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault init
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,489:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , Vault encrypts a known piece of text (
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,490:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,491:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: VAULT
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,491:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,492:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: VERIFY
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,492:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,493:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: TOKEN
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,493:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,494:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: V1
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,494:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,506:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ) with the DB key
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,516:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and saves the encrypted result. When you unlock, it derives the key from your password and tries to decrypt that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,519:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: token. If decryption succeeds and the result matches the known text, the password is correct. If not, the key is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,519:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: wrong, decryption fails, and access is denied.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,520:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Session Management
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,523:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: When unlocked, the three encryption keys live in RAM (Python memory). After 5 minutes of no activity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,524:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (configurable), the session auto-locks: keys are set to 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,524:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: None
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,525:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  and garbage collected. You need the master password
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,526:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: again.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,527:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This means: even if someone gets access to your running Mac while you
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,527:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,528:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re away, the keys will have been wiped
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,529:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: from memory after 5 minutes.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,530:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What Goes to the Cloud vs What Stays Local
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,531:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | What you do | In MCP mode | In standalone mode |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,531:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,532:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|---|---|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,533:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,533:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,534:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,535:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Store my Aadhaar card
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,536:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,537:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | 100% local | 100% local |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,538:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,538:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,539:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What is my Aadhaar number?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,540:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,541:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Claude reads the extracted text
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,542:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,543:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | OpenAI gets text snippet |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,543:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,544:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,544:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,545:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Show me my
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,545:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: passport
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,546:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,546:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | 100% local | 100% local |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,547:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,548:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,548:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,549:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Save my Netflix password
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,549:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,551:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | 100% local, NEVER external | 100% local,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,551:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: NEVER external |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,552:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,553:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,553:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,554:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,554:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,555:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s my Netflix password?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,555:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,556:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | 100% local | 100% local |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,557:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,557:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,558:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,559:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Remember my blood type is O+
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,560:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,560:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,561:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 100% local | 100% local |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,562:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,562:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,562:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,563:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,563:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,563:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s my blood type?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,564:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,564:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | 100% local | 100% local |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,565:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,568:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: In MCP mode, when you ask about a document, Vault returns the extracted text to Claude (the MCP client).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,569:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Claude then reads and reasons over it. The text does go to Anthropic
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,569:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,571:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s API at that point, but your original file never
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,572:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: leaves your machine, and credential data is never exposed this way.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,572:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: How Document Storage Works (Step by Step)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,573:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: When you upload a file (say, a photo of your Aadhaar card):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,573:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1. aadhaar.jpg arrives (raw bytes)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,574:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,575:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          v
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,575:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2. Detect file type → "image"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,576:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,577:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          v
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,577:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3. Tesseract OCR extracts text:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,577:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:    "GOVERNMENT OF INDIA
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,578:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Aadhaar - UID
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,578:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Name: Anindya Gupta
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,579:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     DOB: 15/01/1990
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,579:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Aadhaar No: 1234 5678 9012"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,580:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,580:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     +----+----+
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,581:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     |         |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,581:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     v         v
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,582:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4a. Raw file           4b. Extracted text
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,582:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     encrypted               encrypted
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,583:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     with FILE key           with DB key
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,583:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     → saved as              → stored in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,584:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     uuid.enc                SQLite
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,584:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     |                        |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,585:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     v                        v
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,586:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 5a. Stored in           5b. Also embedded
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,587:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     ~/.vault/data/          as vector in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,588:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     files/                  ChromaDB for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,588:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                             semantic search
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,590:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Auto-categorization kicks in: the keyword 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,590:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,591:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Aadhaar
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,592:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,592:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  is detected, so the document is filed under 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,593:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,593:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: identity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,594:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,594:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: .
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,595:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Later, when you ask 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,595:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,596:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What is my Aadhaar number?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,596:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,597:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: :
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,597:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1. Your question arrives
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,598:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,598:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          v
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,599:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2. ChromaDB semantic search
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,599:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:    finds the Aadhaar document
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,600:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,600:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          v
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,601:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3. Encrypted text is decrypted
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,601:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:    (DB key, in memory only)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,602:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,602:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          v
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,603:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4. Text is returned to the AI
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,604:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:    (Claude via MCP, or OpenAI
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,604:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:    in standalone mode)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,605:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,605:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          v
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,606:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 5. AI reads the text:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,606:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:    "Aadhaar No: 1234 5678 9012"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,607:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,607:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          v
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,607:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 6. Answer: "Your Aadhaar number
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,608:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:    is 1234 5678 9012"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,608:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: How Credential Storage Works
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,610:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Credentials get extra protection. They use a separate encryption key and a completely separate code path that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,611:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: NEVER involves any LLM.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,611:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: You: "My Netflix login is user@email.com, password is secret123"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,612:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,612:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          v
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,612:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Parse with regex:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,613:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   service = "netflix"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,613:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   username = "user@email.com"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,614:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   password = "secret123"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,614:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,615:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     +----+----+
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,615:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     |         |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,616:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     v         v
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,616:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: username      password
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,617:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: encrypted     encrypted
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,618:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: with CRED     with CRED
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,618:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: key           key
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,619:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     |         |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,619:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     +----+----+
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,619:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          v
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Stored in SQLite
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (double encrypted:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  field-level AES + DB-level)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,622:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Retrieval is a direct database lookup. No AI involved:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,622:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: You: "What's my Netflix password?"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,623:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,623:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          v
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,624:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DB query: WHERE service = 'netflix'
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,624:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,625:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          v
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,625:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Decrypt username + password with CRED key
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,626:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,626:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          v
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,627:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Return directly: "user@email.com / secret123"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,628:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: How MCP Communication Works
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: When you talk to Claude in Cursor and it needs your vault:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: You (in Cursor): "What's my Netflix password?"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,630:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,630:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          v
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,631:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Claude (Anthropic API) decides:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,631:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   "I should use the vault_get_credential tool"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,632:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,632:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          v
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,632:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Cursor sends JSON-RPC over stdin to vault-mcp process:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,633:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,633:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     "method": "tools/call",
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,634:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     "params": {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,634:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       "name": "vault_get_credential",
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,635:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:       "arguments": {"service": "netflix"}
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,635:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     }
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,636:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   }
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,636:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,637:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          v
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,637:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault-mcp process (on YOUR Mac):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,638:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   1. Checks session is unlocked
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,638:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   2. Queries encrypted SQLite DB
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,639:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   3. Decrypts credential with CRED key
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,639:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   4. Returns plaintext result
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,640:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,640:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:          v
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,641:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Cursor receives result, Claude shows you:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,641:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   "Your Netflix credentials:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,642:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:    Username: user@email.com
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,642:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:    Password: secret123"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,643:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The vault-mcp process runs locally. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,643:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,647:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s a long-running process that Cursor launches on startup and communicates
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,648:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: with over stdin/stdout. No network server, no ports, no HTTP -- just direct process communication.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,648:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Configuration
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,649:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: After 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,650:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault init
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,650:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , your config lives at 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,651:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ~/.vault/config.yaml
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,651:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: :
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,652:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: llm_provider: openai          # "openai", "anthropic", or "ollama"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,653:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: llm_model: gpt-4o-mini        # cloud model (for standalone CLI/web
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,653:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mode only)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,654:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ollama_model: llama3.1:8b     # local model for paranoid mode
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,655:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: paranoid_mode: false           # true = fully offline
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,655:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: session_timeout: 300           # auto-lock after 5 minutes
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,656:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ocr_enabled: true              # OCR for scanned documents
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,656:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: In MCP mode, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,657:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: llm_provider
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,657:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  and 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,658:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: llm_model
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,660:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  are irrelevant because the MCP client (Claude) handles all the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: AI reasoning. These settings only matter for standalone 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault chat
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,662:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  and 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,662:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault serve
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,663:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  modes.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,664:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Backup and Recovery
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,664:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Create a Backup
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,665:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault backup
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,665:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # Creates: ~/.vault/vault_backup_20260312_143000.vbak
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,666:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The .vbak file is a compressed tar archive of your entire encrypted data directory. It
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,667:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,671:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s safe to store on iCloud Drive,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,672:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Google Drive, a USB stick -- because all the data inside is still AES-256-GCM encrypted. Without your master
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,673:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: password, the backup is unreadable.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,673:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Restore on a New Machine
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,674:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # On the new machine:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,674:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cd ~/vault && pip install -e .
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,675:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault restore ~/path/to/backup.vbak
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,675:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault unlock   # enter your master password
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,675:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # Everything is back
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,676:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If Your Mac is Lost or Stolen
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,677:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,678:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Your data on the stolen Mac is encrypted. Without your master password, it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,678:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,678:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s unreadable.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,679:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,679:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If you have a backup elsewhere, restore it on a new machine and you lose nothing.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,680:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,680:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If you have NO backup, your data is gone forever (but also unreadable by the thief).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,681:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Accessing from Your Phone
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,682:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Right now, Vault runs on your Mac. When your Mac is off, you can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,682:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,683:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t access it. Options for phone access:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,683:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Same Wi-Fi (simplest):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,685:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Run 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,685:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault serve --host 0.0.0.0
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,689:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  and access from your phone
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,689:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,690:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s browser at 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,691:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: http://<your-mac-ip>:8000
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,691:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . Works when both devices are on the same network.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,692:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Tailscale (any network, Mac must be on):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,695:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Install Tailscale on Mac and phone. Access Vault from anywhere via
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,696:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the Tailscale private IP. End-to-end encrypted. Mac needs to be awake.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,696:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Raspberry Pi (always-on, Mac not needed):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,700:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Run Vault on a Pi plugged into your home router. It runs 24/7 on ~3
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,701:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: watts of power. Use Tailscale to access from anywhere. Your Mac becomes just another client.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,702:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Quick Start
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,702:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # 1. Go to the project
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,703:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cd ~/vault
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,703:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # 2. Activate the virtual environment
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,704:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: source .venv/bin/activate
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,705:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # 3. Set your OpenAI key (only needed for standalone CLI/web mode)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,705:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: export OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-key-here
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,706:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # 4. Initialize (first time only)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,707:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault init
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,708:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # 5. For MCP: restart Cursor, and the vault tools are available
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,708:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # 6. For web UI: vault serve, then open http://127.0.0.1:8000
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,709:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # 7. For terminal: vault chat
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,710:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Prerequisites
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,711:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,711:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: macOS
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,712:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  with Apple Silicon (M1/M2/M3/M4) or Intel
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,712:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,713:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Python 3.11+
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,713:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (check with 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,714:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: python3 --version
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,714:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: )
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,715:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,715:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Tesseract OCR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,715:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  for scanned documents: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,716:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: brew install tesseract
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,716:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,717:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OpenAI API key
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,717:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (only for standalone mode, not needed for MCP):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,718:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: export OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,719:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Project Files
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,719:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ~/vault/                            # PROJECT CODE
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,720:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |-- vault/
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,720:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |   |-- __init__.py                 # Package version
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,721:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |   |-- agent.py                    # Brain: intent detect + query
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,722:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: routing
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,722:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |   |-- backup.py                   # Backup/restore logic
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,723:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |   |-- cli.py                      # Terminal commands
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,724:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |   |-- config.py                   # Configuration management
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,724:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |   |-- main.py                     # Web server (FastAPI)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,725:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |   |-- mcp_server.py              # MCP server (17 tools for
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,725:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Claude/Cursor)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,726:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |   |-- security/
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,727:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |   |   |-- encryption.py           # AES-256-GCM, Argon2id,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,727:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: BLAKE2b
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,728:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |   |   |-- session.py              # Session lock/unlock,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,728:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: auto-timeout
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,729:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |   |-- storage/
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,730:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |   |   |-- database.py             # SQLite database with
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,730:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: encrypted fields
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,731:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |   |   |-- file_vault.py           # Encrypted file storage on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,732:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: disk
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,732:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |   |   |-- vector_store.py         # ChromaDB semantic search
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,733:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |   |-- processors/
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,734:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |   |   |-- document.py             # PDF/image text extraction,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,734:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OCR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,735:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |   |   |-- credentials.py          # Credential CRUD (never
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,736:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: touches LLM)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,736:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |   |   |-- memory.py               # Personal facts store
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,737:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |   |-- llm/
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,737:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |   |   |-- router.py               # LLM switching (cloud vs
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,738:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Ollama)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,739:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |   |   |-- prompts.py              # AI prompts (standalone mode
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,739:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: only)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |   |-- web/
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |       |-- static/css/style.css    # Dark theme
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,741:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |       |-- static/js/app.js        # Frontend logic
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,741:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |       |-- templates/*.html        # Chat UI, lock screen, setup
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |-- .venv/                          # Python virtual environment
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,743:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |-- pyproject.toml                  # Package config + dependencies
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,743:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |-- requirements.txt                # Dependencies list
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,744:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |-- README.md                       # Short readme
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,745:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ~/.vault/                           # YOUR DATA (encrypted)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,746:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |-- config.yaml                     # Settings (non-sensitive)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,747:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |-- data/
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,748:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     |-- vault.db                    # Encrypted database
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,748:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     |-- files/                      # Encrypted document files
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,749:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     |-- chroma/                     # Semantic search index
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,750:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     |-- .salt                       # Argon2id salt
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,750:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     |-- .verify_token               # Password verification token
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,752:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ~/.cursor/mcp.json                  # MCP config (tells Cursor
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,753:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: about Vault)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,753:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: FAQ
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,754:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Q: What if I forget my master password?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,755:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,757:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Your data is permanently lost. There is no recovery. This is by design --
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,757:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: if we could recover it, so could an attacker.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,758:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Q: Is my data safe if my Mac is stolen?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,758:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,759:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Yes. Everything under 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,759:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ~/.vault/data/
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  is encrypted with
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: AES-256-GCM. Without your master password, it is computationally infeasible to read.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,762:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Q: Do AI companies see my passwords?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,762:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,765:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: No. Credentials use a completely separate code path with direct
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,766:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: encrypted database lookups. No LLM (whether OpenAI, Anthropic, or local) ever sees your passwords.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,767:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Q: In MCP mode, what does Claude see?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,767:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,780:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Claude sees the results of vault tool calls. For document queries, it sees
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,787:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: extracted text. For credentials, it sees the decrypted username/password (so it can show you). For facts, it sees the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,788:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: value. Claude does NOT see your raw files or your master password. The MCP tool results stay within your Cursor
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,789:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: session.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,789:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Q: Does Claude see document text when I ask questions?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,790:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,790:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Yes, in MCP mode, when you ask 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,791:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,791:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,792:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,792:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s my Aadhaar
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,793:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: number?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,793:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,794:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , Claude calls vault
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,794:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,794:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: read
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,795:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,796:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: document, gets back the extracted text, and reads it to find the answer. That text
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,797:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: goes through Anthropic
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,797:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,798:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s API. If this concerns you, use the standalone CLI with paranoid mode (Ollama) for fully
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,799:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: local processing.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,799:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Q: Can I use this without internet?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,801:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Mostly yes. All storage, retrieval, and credential operations work offline. Only
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,802:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: AI-powered document Q
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,802:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A needs internet (or Ollama for local). In MCP mode, you need internet for Claude, but
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: all vault operations are local.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Q: Can I use both MCP mode and the web UI?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Yes, but not simultaneously from the same vault. The MCP server
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,816:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and the web server are separate processes. They both read from the same encrypted data on disk, but the session
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,816:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (unlock state, keys in memory) is per-process. You
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,817:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,818:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d need to unlock in each one separately.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,818:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Q: How do I move Vault to a new Mac?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Run 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault backup
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , copy the .vbak file, install Vault on the new Mac,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: run 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,822:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault restore
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,823:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , then 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,823:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vault unlock
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,824:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . Copy your 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,824:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ~/.cursor/mcp.json
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,825:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  too if using MCP mode.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,825:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Q: Where does the code live vs where does my data live?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,826:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,827:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Code: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,827:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ~/vault/
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,828:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . Data: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,828:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ~/.vault/
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,829:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . They
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,829:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,831:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re
   DEBUG: 2026-03-12 03:24:47,831:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: separate. You can delete and reinstall the code without losing data.
